  "title": "Service/ Maintenance Technician (Vending Machine) #81365",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: F&B Vending Service</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Vending Maintenance Technician</strong></li><li>Working Location: Bukit Merah (Walk distance from MRT)</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 Days, Monday – Friday (9am – 6pm), Saturday (9am – 12.45pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary (Yearly increment) + Variable Bonus (Profit Sharing)</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct routine checks, servicing, and repairs on vending machines, and resolve any identified issues.</li><li>Refill and top up vending machine items (e.g., sandwiches, drinks) and operational supplies (e.g., coins).</li><li>Diagnose and fix mechanical/ electrical breakdowns quickly to minimise downtime.</li><li>Maintain accurate logs of servicing work completed and machine performance.</li><li>Work closely with the operations team to keep machines running smoothly across the Singapore network.</li><li>Suggest enhancements to improve machine reliability and overall user experience.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Possess valid Singapore Class 2B and Class 3 driving licenses (company vehicle and motorcycle provided).</li><li>Prior experience as a vending machine technician or in a related field service/ maintenance role.</li><li>Strong hands-on technical ability to troubleshoot and repair mechanical and electrical issues.</li><li>Able to communicate professionally with business clients.</li><li>Skills in painting, light brazing, electronics, and refrigeration are required.</li><li>Willing to perform manual physical duties, and occasional midnight delivery/ restocking shifts when required (not often).</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81365 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
